org.streaminer.stream.frequency

Class CountSketch<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.streaminer.stream.frequency.BaseFrequency<T>
      • org.streaminer.stream.frequency.CountSketch<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBaseFrequency<T>, IRichFrequency<T>, ISimpleFrequency<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CountMinSketch

    public class CountSketch<T>
extends BaseFrequency<T>

    Implementation of the CountSketch algorithm from the paper 'Finding frequent items in data streams' written by 'Charikar, M., Chen, K., and Farach-colton, M. (2002)'.

    Author:
    Marcin Skirzynski (main work), Benedikt Kulmann (modifications)

    • Constructor Detail

      • CountSketch

        public CountSketch(int domain,
           int numberOfHashFunctions,
           int numberOfBuckets,
           int k)

        Constructor of the CountSketch algorithm. This construction can take quite a long time since the construction of the hashfunctions is rather time-consuming.

        Parameters:
        domain - The (estim.) domain, i.e. how many different items are expected
        numberOfHashFunctions - The number of hashfunctions which determine a bucket
        numberOfBuckets - The number of buckets where a counter will be maintained
        k - parameter for the top-k variant. If you want to disable the top-k overhead, than set k to 0 or lower
